    "description_full": "The High Conviction Sleeve is a selective, rules-based allocation strategy that prioritizes capital deployment only when market conditions demonstrate clear, repeatable edge. Rather than maintaining continuous exposure, the sleeve evaluates relative behavior to identify periods of highest conviction. When those conditions are present, capital is concentrated into a single high-beta growth position; when they are not, the strategy deliberately stands aside in cash. This disciplined, binary approach emphasizes signal quality over trade frequency, resulting in a high win rate, controlled drawdowns, and strong risk-adjusted performance driven by patience and selectivity rather than constant participation.",
